.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_ObjectAutoGrab
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: It is possible to automatically grab an Interactable Object to a specific controller by applying the Object Auto Grab script to the controller that the object should be grabbed by default.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/026_Controller_ForceHoldObject shows how to automatically grab a sword to each controller and also prevents the swords from being dropped so they are permanently attached to the user's controllers.

methods.name: AutoGrab()
ClearPreviousClone()
methods.summary: The ClearPreviousClone method resets the previous cloned object to null to ensure when the script is re-enabled that a new cloned object is created, rather than the original clone being grabbed again.

events.name: ObjectAutoGrabCompleted
events.summary: Emitted when the object auto grab has completed successfully.
